## Stack (do not substitute without explicit approval)

- Monorepo: Turborepo + **npm workspaces**
- Frontend: Next.js 14 App Router, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, Vercel
- API: NestJS (single gateway), Prisma, class-validator
- Data: Supabase PostgreSQL + RLS + Auth + Storage + pgvector
- Cache/queue: Redis (local in dev, managed in prod â€” not Upstash), BullMQ
- Payments: Stripe + COD

## Scale & performance (1M+ concurrent baseline)

- CDN-first: ISR (60s) for product/category/home; origin only for dynamic/auth
- Stateless API; session/cart/rate-limits in Redis only
- Async anything >200ms (email, embeddings, exports) via BullMQ
- DB: pooled connections (PgBouncer), indexes on hot columns, read replicas later
- No N+1 queries; paginate lists (default 20); select only needed columns
- Images: Supabase CDN transforms + Next.js Image (WebP)

## v2 business rules (non-negotiable)

1. **Seller anonymity**: Buyers never receive `seller_id`, store name, slug, or contact. Use `BuyerProductDTO` + `ProductSerializerInterceptor` on all buyer/guest routes. Buyer app must not import seller types from `shared-types`.
2. **Product ownership**: `seller_owned` | `platform_owned` | `seller_assigned`. Platform-owned ? admin fulfilment, no payout. Only `platform_owned` shows "MarketNest Official" badge.
3. **Roles**: `superadmin` | `seller` | `buyer`. Sellers created by admin only. Guest cart in Redis (7d TTL), merge at checkout.

## Code patterns

- Domain modules in NestJS (`auth`, `products`, `orders`, ï¿½); thin controllers, logic in services
- DTOs + validation on every API input; typed responses; no `any`
- RLS is primary isolation; API guards are secondary (RBAC `@Roles()`)
- Shared types in `packages/shared-types`; buyer barrel excludes seller DTOs
- UI tokens from `packages/tokens` (web coral + mobile green scales â€” see `Design.md`); never hardcode colours/spacing
- Secrets only in env; never commit `.env`

## When adding features

- Map to a user story ID (e.g. BU-05, SA-11) in PR/commit context
- P1 before P2/P3 unless user says otherwise
- Add migration + RLS policy with schema changes
- Update `.env.example` when new env vars are required
